//GOD1PRF:794646 It follows that $j$ is an isomorphism of K onto a subring of L , and it is natural to regard as identical an element $a$ of K and the corresponding element $j(a)$ of L . From now on, therefore, we shall write
claim h_s27_construction_constant_subring :
  subring (multivariate_polynomial_ring K add n)
    (polynomial_addition K add n) (polynomial_multiplication K add mul n)
