admit.
//GOD1PRF:795877 We shall now construct an element of L which is transcendental over K . Put
claim h_s27_construction_indeterminates_members : forall i :e n,
  polynomial_indeterminate K add mul n i
  :e multivariate_polynomial_ring K add n.
admit.
//GOD1PRF:796788 shows that the left-hand side of (11) vanishes only if $a_{0}=a_{1}=a_{2}=\cdots=0$. Consequently X is transcendental over K .
claim h_s27_construction_indeterminates_independent :
