    (polynomial_constant_subring K add mul n) n
    (polynomial_indeterminate K add mul n) coeff ->
  forall exponent :e omega :^: n,
    coeff exponent = polynomial_constant K add mul n (ring_zero K add).
admit.
//GOD1PRF:801097 and since $\mathrm{X}_{n}$ is transcendental over $\mathrm{K}^{\prime}$, it follows that $f_{s}=0$ for all $s \geqslant 0$. But $X_{1}, \ldots, X_{n-1}$ are algebraically independent over $K$, hence we have
claim h_s27_construction_induction_independence :
