admit.
//GOD1PRF:822329 vanishes at every point of K , and since Theorem 1 has already been proved for polynomials in one indeterminate it follows that
claim h_s28_t1_one_variable_specialization_formal_call :
  forall f0 g0 :e multivariate_polynomial_ring K add 1,
    f0 = g0 <-> forall x0 :e K :^: 1,
