//GOD1PRF:864478 In order to be able to manipulate rational fractions it is unnecessary to have recourse to the considerations of section 2 ; those considerations serve only to establish the existence of the field $\mathrm{K}\left(\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right)$. What matters in practice are the properties of this field; in other words, the reader should remember the following assertions and nothing else:\\
claim h_s29_rf_section2_fraction_field_formal_call :
