admit.
//GOD1PRF:864887 (RF 1): the rational fractions in $n$ indeterminates with coefficients in K are the elements of a field denoted by $\mathrm{K}\left(\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right)$;\\
