      (polynomial_multiplication K add mul n)).
admit.
//GOD1PRF:865069 (RF 2) : amongst the rational fractions in $n$ indeterminates with coefficients in K are the polynomials in $n$ indeterminates with coefficients in K ; more precisely, the ring $\mathrm{K}\left[\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right]$ of polynomials in $n$ indeterminates with coefficients in K is a subring of the field $\mathrm{K}\left(\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right)$;\\
