admit.
//GOD1PRF:865463 (RF3): for every rational fraction $f \in \mathrm{~K}\left(\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right)$, there exist two polynomials $p$, $q \in \mathrm{~K}\left[\mathrm{X}_{1}, \ldots, \mathrm{X}_{n}\right]$, with $q \neq 0$, such that
claim h_s29_RF3 : forall x :e rational_function_field K add mul n,
