admit.
//GOD1PRF:865729 Of course, there are many possible ways of writing $f$ as the quotient of two polynomials; for two rational fractions $p^{\prime} / q^{\prime}$ and $p^{\prime \prime} / q^{\prime \prime}$ to be equal, it is necessary and sufficient that $p^{\prime} q^{\prime \prime}=p^{\prime \prime} q^{\prime}$.
claim h_s29_rational_fraction_equality :
  forall p q p' q' :e multivariate_polynomial_ring K add n,
    q <> (fun exponent :e omega :^: n => ring_zero K add) ->
